annotation.TEXT: Yep, there's the keyhole.
Whoops. There goes my shell...
LOL. For a split-second there, I thought the springboard was also intended for getting over this pipe!
And now, let's do the Notepad thing to see the voting results...
This version of the Buoy Base music sounds awesome, by the way.
Could I have reached that without flying?
Lucky stomp there. If you land on an enemy and a springboard at the same time, sometimes you'll get hurt, or sometimes you'll just stomp the enemy and bounce off the springboard unharmed.
I was thinking that might've been a multi-coin block there. Still, a silver P-switch is probably better!
Ooh! Found it! Also, there's a 1-up to go with it, which is quite generous.
Better be careful. I've entered torpedo country.
Wow, did you see that? Both flames jumped right over my shell!
Okay, can I maybe hang on to this flower for more than eight seconds this time?
You didn't think I'd put up a picture of actual barf, did you?
Well, there is this Yoshi coin...
And now to play through the entirety of this level again for the normal exit. Let's listen to the double speed Buoy Base music in the meantime.
Hey there Wiggler. How's it going?
Wait. I want to dive bomb this thing properly!
BGM: Kirby's Adventure - Forest
Whoa! Barely dodged that duder!
Ooh, can I get every coin?
Narrowly avoided that torpedo...
Yeah! Commence victory dive bombs!
D'oh! Well, so much for that flower...
Ooh, that's a tricky Yoshi coin to reach, even for a caped crusader. Maybe if I had a weapon available...
That was unnecessarily risky right there.
There's a yellow ! block. I don't need any mushrooms now, but if I get hit within the next eight seconds, I might come back for it.
Oh, man. Is there anything I can do to stomp the polluted water's rampagin'?
Oh, thanks, Mr. Blue Koopa! That was very kind of you to provide me with this shell!
Up next is Toxic Thicket 2, and I think I'll do it now.
So, yeah. I'm going to assume that the obviously polluted stuff is still death water.
Alright, so I get a bunch of coins and a 1-up as a reward for my Urchin-murdering ways. Not bad.
Whoa, careful.
And this level is done! Hmm... I wonder if it was a good idea to convert the springboard into a feather...
Yeah, I think I'll take that flower. It might come in handy.
Oh, man... Just look at all that polluted muck being dumped into the water...
Okay, there's an Urchin blocking some goodies, and a couple of ice blocks. Gee, I wonder what I should do...
I'm assuming you'd normally use this springboard to reach it, though.
Umm... Sure, I'll go back around for that 1-up.
Alright, so the votes have spoken! GSP is first, and TT1 is second, so I'm heading to the Green Switch Palace first!
Oh, that Chuck is probably going to wake up all the RVFs on me, but not if I fry him to death first!
Yeah! I even managed to pull off a switch jump right afterwards!
Gotta check every pipe... even if it seems silly to...
Hmm... I wonder if there's anything in the sky...
Secret Zone, eh? I think this is just a tiny level where I can pick up goodies, like the Top Secret Area.
Go my green blocks, and fill the world with your greenness!
I don't know why I'm trying to do a stomping combo here...
Just how toxic is this thicket? Let's find out. (Better stock up on Antidotes and Pecha berries, just in case!)
Now, I couldn't honestly remember where that missing Yoshi coin was, so I wasted a little bit of time searching around here.
Huh. No wiggling animation on the stunned koopa. The first time that happened, I thought it might've been related to my powering up timing, but I wasn't in the middle of powering up here.
Aww... No love for Toxic Thicket 3?
Well, I can use it almost anywhere to swim faster, which is nice.
Alright, now since Toxic Thicket 1 got second place, that's where I'm heading next.
BGM: Super Mario Galaxy - Buoy Base Galaxy
Oh, man. This looks dangerous. Better switch to my cape. Also, I believe the keyhole is to my left. Oh, and I see that the death water doesn't hurt the dolphins.
Whoa! Thanks for the heads up! I'm glad the game is kind enough to inform me that this is death water!
I think those coins in front of that last Yoshi coin are normally munchers, so the silver P-switch was needed to reach it.
Could it be in the sky somewhere? I wonder because the game did start giving me capes around here...
What the heck with those flames being immune to the kicked shell? Must be one of those sprite slot things...
And that's it. The cape didn't actually break much. Normally, you'd use the springboard to reveal this note block bridge, and then hit the P-switches.

Hello, and welcome back to Bowser Rampages Again! Last time, I unlocked a few levels, but before I figure out which of them I'm playing next, I've gotta go and replay Rocky Channel 2 to find that Yoshi coin I missed...
Alright, now that I've replayed about 99% of the level, let's head to the right from here and hit the goal.
D'oh! That's okay, because the flower just behind me hadn't despawned yet!
BGM: Shatterhand (NES) - Area A
I was trying for a 50, obviously, but I guess I'll take a 40. And that's more than enough for a 4x speed bonus game!
Oh, hey. A key. I wonder where I can use it...
Alright, now let's start breaking the puzzle with my cape!
Oh, man. So much green... Even the cape feather and hopping flames are green! Hmm... And yeah, I think I'll take a spare cape feather right now.
I couldn't remember if I was going to want an extra shell or not, but this is just a simple puzzle room, so the shell is unnecessary.
Yeah! Sweet! I did fumble a little on the Select button there, but I still accomplished what I wanted to with it, so that I ended up with one flower and one feather.
Yeah, I probably should've kept my reserve flower from before. Fireballs are generally more useful than cape spins in the sea.
Up next in this direction is Toxic House. Should I play that level next? Or should I go back and play Toxic Thicket 3 next? Vote now, and we'll find out next time!
To be continued...
I hope that water is clean!
Well, at least I got a replacement power up, in the form of a more useful flower here.
Yep! I wonder how I overlooked that spot last time... Well, whatever.
Argh! I hate how Torpedo Teds do that and remain harmful after being clobbered by something! Why couldn't Nintendo have just bothered programming them to die properly?
